# iSenhas Source Available License (ISAL) v1.1

Copyright (c) 2026 Davi Orzechowski

## 1. Purpose

This repository is publicly available to provide transparency,
security auditing, and educational inspection of the iSenhas iOS client.

This software is **source-available**, not open source.

## 2. Permitted Use

You are allowed to:

* View and study the source code
* Audit the security implementation
* Compile and run the software for personal use
* Report vulnerabilities or suggest improvements
* Use limited portions of the code for non-commercial educational purposes

## 3. Restrictions

You may NOT:

* Use this software or modified versions for commercial purposes
* Create or distribute competing password manager applications
* Publish applications derived from this code to any app store
* Offer hosted or SaaS services based on this software
* Redistribute modified versions under a different product identity
* Remove copyright or license notices

Commercial use requires explicit written permission from the copyright holder.

## 4. Name and Branding

The name "iSenhas", associated branding, and visual identity are
reserved for the original project.

Permission to use this name or represent derivative software as
official iSenhas software is not granted.

## 5. Backend and Infrastructure

This repository intentionally excludes backend services,
production APIs, infrastructure components, and operational systems.

Reproducing production services is outside the scope of this license.

## 6. Security Disclosure

Security vulnerabilities must be reported privately to:

[davi@isenhas.com.br](mailto:davi@isenhas.com.br)

Public disclosure before coordinated remediation is discouraged.

